Just did our first preview of @sweeneytoddbway and whewww…

17 years ago today, I made my Broadway debut. Today, I rehearsed @sweeneytoddbway in the infamous @hamiltonmusical King’s College.

I am filled with gratitude for the success I’ve had, and I also am filled with gratitude for the in betweens: the moments where I questioned if this was the path for me, the moments where I didn’t find joy in performing, when my joy was found through my friendships and not being onstage, when I was told “no,” when I cried big tears over rejection, when I made mistakes, lost friends, missed weddings and holidays with family, and the times where I didn’t know how I would pay rent between gigs.

This life is not always glamorous, and the glam moments are not always what make you who you are. I think 11 year old me would be proud to know that I am happy and performing on Broadway, but I also finally have accepted that crying and being unhappy sometimes is ok. And I have other passions. And I have animals and friends. And that all those things can exist.

And I think she would also appreciate knowing that her mom is still the best. 😉

@alprakken closes his first Broadway show today, but he’s so freakin talented, he’s too busy doing another show, and has to miss the last performance. I am so proud to be his partner. He is the most supportive, loyal, and patient person. He shows up for the people he loves. He’s waited so patiently for this moment. I’m so glad we could all show up for YOU, and celebrate the immense talent and human you are. Your onstage Broadway debut was something i will never ever ever forget. You are transcendent off and onstage. This is only the beginning and I love you to the moon and back. Now please come home so we can figure out what to do with this poster. 😍🥰🤍

The @sweeneytoddbway cast album is out and it was such a bucket list moment- to record this music, with this orchestra, with this company, with this music team. To hear my voice on this recording is incredibly surreal and I am so thrilled it’s out for everyone to enjoy now! 

The third slide is of the audition cut we had to sing for our initial tape for the show. I looked at it while we were in Power Station and got real real emotional thinking of that day in September 2022 when i smudged my makeup and stood in front of a blue backdrop dreaming about being in this production. I love @sweeneytoddbway !!!!!!!
